To compile libmusical, do the following:

0. Get Prerequisites
   * C++ compiler. libmusical is expected to compile using any recent
     C++ compiler. There are no platform-dependent parts.
   * For using the provided makefile, GNU Make is required.
   * cmake > 2.6 (get it from: http://www.cmake.org)

1. Download the latest version from:
   https://sourceforge.net/projects/libmusical/files

2. Extract the archive.

3. In subdirectory "build" invoke cmake ../.

4. In the same subdirectory invoke make, and optionally make install

5. To use the library include "libmusical.h" in your source code and
   link against libmusical.

